1
00:00:10,750 --> 00:00:13,292
You got it all wrong.
I was looking for you.

2
00:00:13,375 --> 00:00:15,250
-Yeah. to kill us.
-No, I want to help.

3
00:00:17,208 --> 00:00:20,292
I don't know what you or the agency thinks
that you're doing here, but it's--

4
00:00:20,375 --> 00:00:23,375
Well, I don't know
what a Lieutenant Governor actually is,

5
00:00:23,458 --> 00:00:25,750
so I guess we're even, aren't we, Juan?

6
00:00:26,792 --> 00:00:28,458
All of this is not supposed to be

7
00:00:28,542 --> 00:00:30,750
in a warehouse in Brooklyn,
it's supposed to be on its way

8
00:00:30,833 --> 00:00:31,958
to Guinea-Bissau.

9
00:00:32,042 --> 00:00:34,417
-[groans]
-[Fisk] Your shipment will be delivered.

10
00:00:34,500 --> 00:00:36,708
I would ask that you practice patience!

11
00:00:37,417 --> 00:00:39,167
[Daniel] You really don't have to
do this, man.

12
00:00:39,250 --> 00:00:40,667
I don't even know what I did.
But whatever it was,

13
00:00:40,750 --> 00:00:42,792
-I probably deserve it.
-Get out of the car, Daniel.

14
00:00:42,875 --> 00:00:44,792
We work for a man
who can change your life.

15
00:00:44,875 --> 00:00:46,583
And all he asks in return is loyalty.

16
00:00:46,667 --> 00:00:47,792
Make a choice.

17
00:00:49,667 --> 00:00:51,750
Javi, I need you to do something for me.

18
00:00:52,208 --> 00:00:53,375
[Javi] Yo, you're BB.

19
00:00:53,458 --> 00:00:55,458
-Can I get a pic?
-Yeah, for sure. Come on.

20
00:00:59,667 --> 00:01:01,125
[Dex] First, you try to kill me,

21
00:01:01,208 --> 00:01:02,917
and then you try to save me.

22
00:01:03,792 --> 00:01:06,125
I'm trying to save you
because I tried to kill you.

23
00:01:06,208 --> 00:01:07,208
Little help?

24
00:01:09,542 --> 00:01:10,750
Vanessa?

25
00:01:11,333 --> 00:01:14,083
-Nurse!
-[EKG flatlining]

26
00:01:54,292 --> 00:01:56,708
[Dr. Merati]
"They that love beyond the world

27
00:01:57,542 --> 00:01:59,208
"cannot be separated by it.

28
00:02:01,667 --> 00:02:03,750
"Death cannot kill what never dies."

29
00:02:06,917 --> 00:02:11,000
-I'm deeply sorry for your loss, Mr. Fisk.
-[sobs]

30
00:02:12,542 --> 00:02:15,583
Even in her final moments,
she was the brightest of lights.

31
00:02:18,042 --> 00:02:19,833
Take solace in knowing that she...

32
00:02:20,417 --> 00:02:21,625
is at rest now.

33
00:02:24,833 --> 00:02:27,833
Gone to the beautiful darkness
that awaits us all.

34
00:02:34,542 --> 00:02:36,125
It has been a sad honor...

35
00:02:37,583 --> 00:02:39,833
accompanying you
on this journey, Mr. Fisk.

36
00:02:56,250 --> 00:02:59,250
[groaning] Mr. Fisk.

37
00:02:59,750 --> 00:03:01,292
[chokes] Mr. Fisk--

38
00:03:01,542 --> 00:03:02,958
Mr. Fisk.

39
00:03:03,042 --> 00:03:05,250
-[choking]
-[bones cracking]

40
00:03:52,292 --> 00:03:54,792
-[bell tolling]
-[♪ somber music playing]

41
00:04:29,917 --> 00:04:32,958
"Requiem aeternam dona ei, domine

42
00:04:33,958 --> 00:04:36,375
"et lux perpetua luceat ei.

43
00:04:36,833 --> 00:04:38,375
"Requiescat en pace."

44
00:04:38,542 --> 00:04:39,542
Amen.

45
00:04:39,875 --> 00:04:41,750
"Domine Iesu Christe,

46
00:04:43,375 --> 00:04:44,833
"Rex gloriae

47
00:04:45,750 --> 00:04:47,875
"libera animas omnium

48
00:04:47,958 --> 00:04:50,000
"fidelium defunctorum...

49
00:04:56,917 --> 00:04:59,083
"De poenis inferni..."

50
00:05:02,625 --> 00:05:03,625
Nothing here.

51
00:05:03,708 --> 00:05:05,167
[priest] "Et de profundo lacu..."

52
00:05:05,250 --> 00:05:06,333
[chuckles] Okay.

53
00:05:11,042 --> 00:05:12,583
[priest] "Libera eas

54
00:05:12,792 --> 00:05:14,208
"de ore leoni."

55
00:05:15,833 --> 00:05:18,042
Thank you, Mayor Fisk.

56
00:05:21,708 --> 00:05:24,667
[priest] "Ne absorbeat eas tartarus...

57
00:05:33,542 --> 00:05:35,417
"Ne cadant in obscurum."

58
00:05:36,750 --> 00:05:37,750
[priest] Amen.

59
00:06:06,042 --> 00:06:07,667
[whispers indistinctly]

60
00:07:08,417 --> 00:07:10,875
[♪ theme music playing]

61
00:08:21,292 --> 00:08:23,458
[female automated voice] On your mark.

62
00:08:23,542 --> 00:08:24,542
Get set.

63
00:08:24,917 --> 00:08:25,917
Spin!

64
00:08:27,542 --> 00:08:29,042
Oh, nice try.

65
00:08:29,125 --> 00:08:30,333
Spin again.

66
00:08:38,542 --> 00:08:39,667
Let's go for more.

67
00:08:39,750 --> 00:08:40,875
On your mark.

68
00:08:40,958 --> 00:08:42,542
Get ready. Spin!

69
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:44,500
Way to go!

70
00:08:44,583 --> 00:08:46,250
[man] Hey, there she is! [groans]

71
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:51,708
-[man grunting]
-[device beeping]

72
00:08:54,250 --> 00:08:56,417
[man groaning]

73
00:09:02,042 --> 00:09:03,958
[man screaming in pain]

74
00:09:05,958 --> 00:09:10,250
[beeping intensifies]

75
00:09:10,333 --> 00:09:11,333
[Jessica] Honey.

76
00:09:13,750 --> 00:09:16,375
-This is not a toy.
-[clicks, beeping stops]

77
00:09:20,083 --> 00:09:22,333
He's lost a lotta blood,
but I got the bullet out.

78
00:09:22,417 --> 00:09:24,667
If he can keep it clean
and prevent infection,

79
00:09:24,750 --> 00:09:26,333
which is a big "if,"

80
00:09:26,417 --> 00:09:27,417
he should be fine.

81
00:09:27,875 --> 00:09:28,875
Angela,

82
00:09:29,333 --> 00:09:30,708
[in Spanish] pasame esa venda por favor.

83
00:09:30,792 --> 00:09:32,500
[in English]
Thank you, Soledad. Good to know.

84
00:09:32,583 --> 00:09:35,458
[Soledad] I'm really doing my best here.
But he could really use a hospital.

85
00:09:35,542 --> 00:09:36,542
No.

86
00:09:36,833 --> 00:09:38,625
[Daredevil] That would sign
his death warrant.

87
00:09:38,708 --> 00:09:39,708
Maybe we should.

88
00:09:39,792 --> 00:09:41,875
-Karen.
-[Karen] What? I'm not behind this.

89
00:09:41,958 --> 00:09:44,083
He should be dead
or in one of Fisk's dungeons, not here.

90
00:09:44,167 --> 00:09:45,667
-Understood.
-[Angela] She's right.

91
00:09:45,750 --> 00:09:47,083
The whole city is popping off
'cause of what he did.

92
00:09:47,167 --> 00:09:48,333
[Daredevil] It was an accident.

93
00:09:48,708 --> 00:09:49,708
[Karen] This time.

94
00:09:51,417 --> 00:09:53,458
Hey. What's goin' on out there?

95
00:09:54,250 --> 00:09:55,917
[Angela] Lotta people
crying their eyes out,

96
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:57,917
throwing thoughts and prayers
about the Mayor's wife.

97
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:59,042
But not everyone.

98
00:09:59,125 --> 00:10:00,125
[Angela] Not even close.

99
00:10:00,208 --> 00:10:02,292
Even more people are pissed,
and not at him.

100
00:10:02,958 --> 00:10:05,458
The raids and people disappearing,
it's worse than ever.

101
00:10:05,542 --> 00:10:07,833
There's a lotta talk
about the vigil at City Hall.

102
00:10:08,125 --> 00:10:09,125
Like people,

103
00:10:09,542 --> 00:10:10,542
our people.

104
00:10:11,167 --> 00:10:12,167
Sounds like trouble.

105
00:10:12,250 --> 00:10:13,417
[speaking Spanish] Si Titi.

106
00:10:22,042 --> 00:10:23,167
[Karen, in English] Listen,

107
00:10:23,250 --> 00:10:25,625
I need you to promise me
that you're gonna stay low.

108
00:10:26,458 --> 00:10:28,208
You're gonna stay safe, okay?

109
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:31,125
[Angela sighs]

110
00:10:33,417 --> 00:10:35,000
[footsteps retreating]

111
00:10:35,083 --> 00:10:37,042
[door opens]

112
00:10:37,333 --> 00:10:39,000
[door closes]

113
00:10:43,083 --> 00:10:45,042
-Any news from Christofi?
-[Karen] No.

114
00:10:45,125 --> 00:10:47,792
But my source should drop
the Red Hook testimony soon.

115
00:10:47,875 --> 00:10:50,417
Good. That'll help
with the hearts and minds.

116
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:51,500
[Karen] Oh, we've got those.

117
00:10:51,583 --> 00:10:53,167
The Resistance grows every day.

118
00:10:53,875 --> 00:10:55,958
Whenever someone
gets locked up or disappears.

119
00:10:56,042 --> 00:10:57,750
-It's not enough, we need more.
-How do you mean?

120
00:10:57,833 --> 00:10:59,250
[Karen sighs]

121
00:11:03,333 --> 00:11:04,667
Okay. Uh...

122
00:11:05,917 --> 00:11:06,917
[clears throat]

123
00:11:09,458 --> 00:11:11,958
Do you remember that night
at the Clinton Street Church?

124
00:11:16,583 --> 00:11:19,417
He killed Father Lantom and then
he hurt you so bad, I actually

125
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:22,167
-thought I'd lost you for a minute.
-Yeah. Yeah, I remember.

126
00:11:26,792 --> 00:11:29,792
So you told me that you were gonna
kill Fisk and I told you not to.

127
00:11:30,333 --> 00:11:32,375
-That I knew how--
-Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, I remember.

128
00:11:35,542 --> 00:11:36,667
What if I was wrong?

129
00:11:37,417 --> 00:11:38,542
Karen, please stop it.

130
00:11:38,625 --> 00:11:41,458
Can't you see that is
what separates us from him?

131
00:11:41,542 --> 00:11:44,542
-Are we really still that separate?
-Yes, we are! We are separate.

132
00:11:45,042 --> 00:11:46,583
It is not up to us to take life.

133
00:11:46,667 --> 00:11:48,083
I know, I know!

134
00:11:48,167 --> 00:11:50,792
All right, I pay every day
for what I did to Wesley.

135
00:11:50,875 --> 00:11:52,708
I still have fucking nightmares!

136
00:11:57,667 --> 00:11:59,625
But the difference is I don't regret it.

137
00:11:59,708 --> 00:12:00,750
It was him or me.

138
00:12:00,833 --> 00:12:03,375
And what if that's what it's like with you
and Fisk? Him or you?

139
00:12:03,458 --> 00:12:06,833
What if this doesn't end
until one of you goes down?

140
00:12:06,917 --> 00:12:08,750
I can't think about it that way.

141
00:12:08,833 --> 00:12:10,083
[Karen] Well, you're gonna have to.

142
00:12:10,167 --> 00:12:12,667
He has proven that he will not hesitate!

143
00:12:16,833 --> 00:12:18,750
This isn't-- It's not-- This isn't you.

144
00:12:18,833 --> 00:12:20,125
-It's not you.
-[phone buzzes]

145
00:12:31,958 --> 00:12:32,958
-It's her.
-Where?

146
00:12:34,125 --> 00:12:35,292
310, Garnet Street.

147
00:12:35,375 --> 00:12:36,375
Okay.

148
00:12:37,917 --> 00:12:39,042
What do we do about him?

149
00:12:42,708 --> 00:12:44,458
Vengeance isn't justice, Karen.

150
00:12:45,833 --> 00:12:46,833
Yeah.

151
00:12:48,375 --> 00:12:49,375
I won't be long.

152
00:12:49,792 --> 00:12:50,833
Hey...

153
00:13:00,792 --> 00:13:02,000
[door opens]

154
00:13:04,458 --> 00:13:05,583
[door closes]

155
00:13:16,958 --> 00:13:19,333
Mayor Fisk, I just wanted to say how--

156
00:13:19,417 --> 00:13:20,958
[people chattering indistinctly]

157
00:13:25,417 --> 00:13:28,292
[Governor] With Vanessa, at least I had
a sense someone had his ear,

158
00:13:28,375 --> 00:13:29,583
someone could rein him in.

159
00:13:29,667 --> 00:13:31,333
I wouldn't have relied on that much.

160
00:13:31,417 --> 00:13:32,917
Pressure on my office is immense.

161
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:35,500
I'm getting it from all sides,
the raids, the Task Force.

162
00:13:35,583 --> 00:13:38,792
Well, I don't see him budging.

163
00:13:38,875 --> 00:13:40,208
Not after this.

164
00:13:40,292 --> 00:13:41,958
Well, he may not have a choice.

165
00:13:43,417 --> 00:13:44,417
What does that mean?

166
00:13:44,500 --> 00:13:46,708
[LT. Governor Gomez]
She said this was gonna be her last term.

167
00:13:46,792 --> 00:13:48,125
And then you'd get the nod?

168
00:13:48,208 --> 00:13:50,750
Yeah, she promised to support
my candidacy. Yes.

169
00:13:51,542 --> 00:13:53,417
You know, where I'm from,

170
00:13:53,958 --> 00:13:57,667
the lady gets to keep the crown right up
until the big man upstairs comes along.

171
00:13:57,750 --> 00:13:58,750
Yeah?

172
00:13:59,375 --> 00:14:02,000
Well, where you're from,
spotted dick is a dessert.

173
00:14:02,083 --> 00:14:04,625
-[chuckles softly]
-This is not a monarchy, Cashman.

174
00:14:06,208 --> 00:14:07,458
[Buck] Are you sure about that?

175
00:14:07,542 --> 00:14:09,417
You've waited patiently, haven't you?

176
00:14:09,500 --> 00:14:10,917
You've been a loyal servant.

177
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:12,708
-Yeah, you're damn right.
-Mmm.

178
00:14:14,083 --> 00:14:15,750
Well, why wait for the big man then?

179
00:14:16,417 --> 00:14:18,750
You once told me
you'd never run for higher office.

180
00:14:18,833 --> 00:14:20,583
You know I can't stomach the campaign.

181
00:14:23,583 --> 00:14:25,458
What if I told you, you wouldn't have to?

182
00:14:26,250 --> 00:14:27,875
So, when were you going to tell me?

183
00:14:27,958 --> 00:14:29,000
Tell you what?

184
00:14:29,583 --> 00:14:30,625
Happy birthday.

185
00:14:31,250 --> 00:14:34,167
I guess I'm not really feeling
the birthday this year, you know?

186
00:14:34,667 --> 00:14:35,917
I need to be here for him.

187
00:14:37,833 --> 00:14:40,042
I don't think you really can be.

188
00:14:40,583 --> 00:14:43,042
Come on. All right, where are we going
tonight? What are we doing?

189
00:14:43,125 --> 00:14:45,750
Um, we're doing nothing. Nowhere.

190
00:14:45,833 --> 00:14:47,000
Why are you lying to me?

191
00:14:47,083 --> 00:14:48,833
Why are you keeping tabs
on my personal life?

192
00:14:48,917 --> 00:14:52,458
Daniel, it's your birthday.
I put it in my phone calendar, you psycho.

193
00:14:54,792 --> 00:14:55,875
[grunts softly]

194
00:14:57,958 --> 00:14:58,958
I get it.

195
00:14:59,333 --> 00:15:00,667
It's dudes only, right?

196
00:15:01,042 --> 00:15:02,833
Luger's? Flashdancers?

197
00:15:02,917 --> 00:15:04,417
My mother's house.

198
00:15:06,667 --> 00:15:07,667
Seriously?

199
00:15:08,042 --> 00:15:09,667
-Yeah.
-[chuckles softly]

200
00:15:10,583 --> 00:15:12,083
Wait, that's really sweet.

201
00:15:12,167 --> 00:15:13,917
[Daniel] Oh, well, I'm glad you think so.

202
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:16,167
What if I came with?

203
00:15:16,250 --> 00:15:17,667
To my ma's house?

204
00:15:18,583 --> 00:15:20,875
You actually wanna come to Staten Island?

205
00:15:20,958 --> 00:15:22,000
Yeah.

206
00:15:22,500 --> 00:15:23,500
I do.

207
00:15:23,583 --> 00:15:25,042
-Uh...
-[Buck] Miss Urich.

208
00:15:25,875 --> 00:15:27,042
Lovely to see you.

209
00:15:27,125 --> 00:15:28,125
Everything good?

210
00:15:29,042 --> 00:15:31,542
You do always seem to be
where the action is, don't you?

211
00:15:31,958 --> 00:15:34,292
Well, that's
what journalists do, Mr. Cashman.

212
00:15:34,375 --> 00:15:35,875
Journalists, right.

213
00:15:36,250 --> 00:15:38,208
Do you mind
if I borrow Daniel for a second?

214
00:15:38,292 --> 00:15:39,958
Just a quick word.

215
00:15:40,833 --> 00:15:42,583
Sure. Of course.

216
00:15:42,667 --> 00:15:43,667
Thanks.

217
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:45,000
Shall we?

218
00:15:51,208 --> 00:15:53,000
-Fuck.
-Daniel, Daniel,

219
00:15:53,083 --> 00:15:55,667
-you need to pull yourself together.
-What we did last night was insane.

220
00:15:55,750 --> 00:15:57,083
It was an order,

221
00:15:57,167 --> 00:15:59,708
and it is behind you,
and you move on, okay?

222
00:16:00,292 --> 00:16:02,667
Listen to me, our little nature walk
was the price of admission.

223
00:16:02,750 --> 00:16:04,167
You're in the big time now.

224
00:16:05,667 --> 00:16:06,958
And the big time

225
00:16:07,042 --> 00:16:08,292
will take care of you.

226
00:16:11,417 --> 00:16:13,792
-[sighs] God.
-If...

227
00:16:14,750 --> 00:16:16,125
you take care of it.

228
00:16:16,208 --> 00:16:17,208
[scoffs] What do you mean?

229
00:16:17,667 --> 00:16:18,667
What?

230
00:16:22,708 --> 00:16:23,708
Our friend, BB.

231
00:16:24,417 --> 00:16:25,542
What about her?

232
00:16:25,625 --> 00:16:27,708
Daniel, I know you're fond of her.

233
00:16:28,542 --> 00:16:30,792
But I think you're letting it
cloud your judgment.

234
00:16:30,875 --> 00:16:32,542
Well, she's not the leak.

235
00:16:32,625 --> 00:16:34,667
-Okay, and do you have proof?
-I don't need it.

236
00:16:34,750 --> 00:16:36,708
Well, I do, and more importantly,
the Mayor does.

237
00:16:39,458 --> 00:16:41,375
Sounds like you two
have plans for tonight.

238
00:16:41,458 --> 00:16:44,375
Yeah, but with everything going on,
I'm just gonna blow it off.

239
00:16:44,458 --> 00:16:45,458
Don't.

240
00:16:46,042 --> 00:16:49,042
Have you ever heard of
the Barium Meal Test?

241
00:16:49,125 --> 00:16:51,625
Yeah, it's like a meal plan or something.

242
00:16:51,708 --> 00:16:53,292
Like Paleo, my mom's on it.

243
00:16:53,375 --> 00:16:55,125
No, Daniel, it's... it's not a meal plan.

244
00:16:55,208 --> 00:16:56,458
More of a technique

245
00:16:56,875 --> 00:16:58,625
developed by my former colleagues.

246
00:16:59,500 --> 00:17:00,917
In order to find a mole,

247
00:17:01,417 --> 00:17:04,125
you must first offer them something
to out themselves with.

248
00:17:04,208 --> 00:17:05,208
Yeah?

249
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:06,500
Yeah.

250
00:17:07,917 --> 00:17:09,458
Feed her something false.

251
00:17:10,458 --> 00:17:12,000
See if it resurfaces.

252
00:17:12,708 --> 00:17:13,958
You see, barium

253
00:17:14,292 --> 00:17:16,875
glows like a light in the darkness.

254
00:17:17,875 --> 00:17:18,875
You with me?

255
00:17:19,667 --> 00:17:20,750
I am.

256
00:17:21,500 --> 00:17:22,792
Good man.

257
00:17:23,833 --> 00:17:24,833
Oh.

258
00:17:26,083 --> 00:17:27,583
